GUARDTHEROCK settled inside keeping tabs on the engaging threesome tracking throughout the turn, began to take closer order at the quarter pole, surged on the fence in upper stretch, chased the winner but to no avail to the wire and stubbornly held besting the rest in the end. CONTRIVANCE prompted three deep down the backside, forced the pace three wide outside through the turn, was in the hunt between horses in lane four at the top of the stretch, drifted out driving to the wire at the eighth pole and was gaining late just missing second money in the end. BE ON NOTICE was in a good spot outside runners tracking the contesting trio up front down the backstretch and throughout the turn, was roused to go on shifting outside turning for home five wide for clear run, was steadied when losing its path at the furlong pole and could not regroup in time to threaten at the wire. ZODIAC BEACH broke with the field but had no early foot trailing down the backside, could see the field but was starting to gain on rivals on the turn and showed some late interest passing weary foes down the lane. OH PEANUTS stalked near the rear on the rail, made no progression running inside throughout the turn and could not get involved in the drive to the finish. SQUEEZETHESHARMAN was off a step slow to begin, then was hustled between horses to have a slim advantage at the half mile marker, was roused for more to keep up with the other contesting rivals up front on either side at the quarter pole, offered little response and stopped on the fence at the furlong marker. RACE.FOOTNOTES: PERHAPS TONIGHT (IRE) settled off the pace shifting in, raced off the leaders three wide between on the turn, waited briefly near the five-sixteenths, was in a tad tight at the quarter pole then came out seven wide in upper stretch, quickened once clear, taking the lead about the eighth pole and forged clear. KEYFLOWER (FR) tracked just off the leaders from inside, came out five wide in upper stretch, was in contention coming to the eighth pole, was no match for the winner, just saved the place. BATYAH settled at the rear racing off the inside in the four path on the turn, rallied between runners four to five wide in the stretch, missed second. PEMBERLEY settled mid-pack off the pace, kept on inside to improve position late. TOERIS soon lead, set the pace racing very wide early, moved nearer but still off the rail heading to the turn, was headed leaving the turn, fought back to retake a narrow and brief lead past the quarter pole but could not sustain the effort and lacked the needed late kick. SILVER MAGNATIZED switched off the inside heading into the turn, raced between foes toward the back four wide, swung out ten wide turning for home, ran on mildly. MY GIRL SKY stalked just off the leaders, encouraged along about the seven-sixteenths, moved out from three to five wide on the turn and wider still for the drive, failed to rally. WHIMSICAL DANCE stalked from outside just off the leader, bid three wide coming past the five-sixteenths taking a narrow lead, flattened out past the quarter and faded. MYRISKYAFFAIR raced outside at the back five to seven wide through the turn advancing a bit, came out a bit further into upper stretch, failed to menace.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: AIM FOR THE SKY was hustled to get the lead down the backside, set the fractions while hounded outside running on the turn, edged away from the chasing rival on the fence at the furlong marker and had just enough left in reserve to hold off the closer at the finish. FORESTER'S FORTUNE stalked close to the back of the pack in the beginning, saved ground on the turn waiting behind a wall of runners at the quarter pole, found a seam in the four path in the final eighth and closed with a flurry late to just miss at the finish. FOUR ACES HIGH chased the frontrunner down the back straight, pressed the winner outside through the turn, battle three wide up front down the lane and gave way grudgingly nearing the wire settling for third in the end. WARP RIDE stalked near the rear five deep down the backside, roused five wide on the turn making little progress, angled out in the seven path at the top of the stretch and closed late for a minor share in the final furlong. GALVASTON tracked the front duo three wide down the back straightaway, chased the leading pair two wide on turn to be in range straightening out for home, fought on through the stretch but faded in the final seventy yards. TRICKY MAGICIAN tracked the front pair four deep down the backstretch, lost ground to rivals running four wide throughout the turn, angled outside six wide for the finish and ran on mildly between horses to the wire. SPITE STORE was checked mildly on the fence to be shuffled back some at the half inside, was in tight fighting for position between runners in midfield on the turn, rallied to be in the mix for a share two wide straightening out for the drive, dug in between rivals in upper stretch but faded in late nearing the wire. WESTERN TROUBLE was pinched at the start trailing down the backside, could still see the field through the turn, had no room to run looking for a seam in upper stretch and could not get involved running to the wire. FEELTHEBEAT was on the rail watching the top two runners down the backside, kept pace on the fence keeping a close eye on the dueling leaders through the turn, was roused inside having clear run at the top of the lane but lacked a bid in the drive to the wire. GHOUL (BRZ) was reined back five deep in midfield at the half, improved making a mild run three wide between runners with five sixteenths to go, continued to be scrubbed on entering the stretch to have a chance for a small piece of the prize five wide, could not offer a finish and tired in the last eighth.
